text: Mangrove Swamps on the Klang Island Klang Island ( is an island in Klang District, Selangor, Malaysia with an area of 2.70 km², covered by mangrove swamps. It is the largest island in the district after Indah Island, and the third-largest island of Selangor. It is currently uninhabited. Category:Nature sites of Selangor Category:Islands of Selangor
title: Klang Island
